commit.message:
Update DTLB_cache_table for Kaby Lake

Two of the descriptors used by Kaby Lake are listed as telling us about
two different things, both 1GB and 2MB pages.  Tell the user about both
things, although this is really a disgusting hack.  Text taken from the
December 2023 edition of the Intel SDM Volume 2A.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Wilcox (Oracle) <willy@infradead.org>
Remove unneeded ]
Remove /n from PentiumIII serial number in cpudata struct

Fix braces-around-scalar warnings from gcc12.

gcc12 introduced a new set of warnings that look like:

vendors/amd/powernow.c: In function ‘get_main_pll_fid’:
vendors/amd/powernow.c:142:16: warning: braces around scalar initializer
  142 |         struct pci_filter filter_nb_misc = { -1, -1, -1, -1, 0x1022, 0x1703 PCI_FILTER_ANYCLASS};

These come from a workaround for back-compat with old pcilib versions.
Remove that workaround completely, and just use named initializers,
which will automatically zero the rest of the struct for those not
explicitly named.
Add recognition of Zen3 Ryzen7

Intel model updates

Based on 6.2-rc7 Linux kernel

Update Intel fam6 products

Based on mappings in 5.19 Linux kernel.

Round units in cache info output

Instead of printing
 L3 Unified Cache: 8192KB, 16-way associative, 64 byte line size

Print the more readable
 L3 Unified Cache: 8MB, 16-way associative, 64 byte line size
Fix recognition of 4790K

intel: fix off by one in previous cacheinfo change

Willy pointed out an off-by-one.

intel: Add support for CPUID leaf 0x18

If CPUID leaf 2 returns descriptor 0xfe, we have to use CPUID leaf
0x18 to decode the TLB descriptors.  Tested with a Tiger Lake, which
reports:

TLB info
 L1 Instruction TLB: 4KB pages, 8-way associative, 128 entries
 L1 Instruction TLB: 4MB/2MB pages, 8-way associative, 16 entries
 L1 Store Only TLB: 1GB/4MB/2MB/4KB pages, fully associative, 16 entries
 L1 Load Only TLB: 4KB pages, 4-way associative, 64 entries
 L1 Load Only TLB: 4MB/2MB pages, 4-way associative, 32 entries
 L1 Load Only TLB: 1GB pages, fully associative, 8 entries
 L2 Unified TLB: 4MB/2MB/4KB pages, 8-way associative, 1024 entries

Signed-off-by: Matthew Wilcox (Oracle) <willy@infradead.org>

No more periodic versioned releases.

No more tagging.
Tarball target left for convenience.
update intel codenames/models
gcc-8 fix
rename release target to tarball
bump minimum for -Werror to gcc 6.3
add tag target

Make cpuid-freebsd.c:cpuid() handle top word of idx as count (%ecx), same as
cpuid-linux.c:cpuid() does.

Make native_cpuid() handle top word of idx as count (%ecx), same as
cpuid-linux.c:cpuid() does.

Fix vendor/inte/identify-family6-extended.c::get_namestring() to print
cpu mode name correcty. When I tested on Kaby Lake machine, it shows:

	CPU Model (x86info's best guess): Unknown model.

Even though it has 0x9e. This diff fix the problem (for ONLYMODEL flag).
After fix, it shows:

	CPU Model (x86info's best guess): [Kabylake desktop]

It also fixes ONLYMHZ flag though it's not used.
amd: Identify Family 17h model CPUs

Makefile: Use pkg-config libpci location

Fixes build on FreeBSD and other systems that install libpci to
/usr/local.
handle failure from enumerate_cpus
handle null EBDA pointer.

Add NetBSD support. Note that NetBSD has not API to access MSR register
from userland.

- Add Atom E3500.
- Add Atom X3-C3000 [Silvermont].
Add 0x64, 0xa0, 0xc3 and 0xc4 into DTLB_cache_table[].

- Add PREFETCHW instruction flag.
- Add Hardware Duty Cycling flag.
- Add HW-controlled performance states (HWP) flags.
add Knights Mill Xeon Phi.

Add exact steppings and complete list of all bloomfield cores.

The information is taken from page 19 of the document 320836-036US
"Intel CoreTM i7-900 Desktop Processor Extreme Edition Series and Intel
CoreTM i7-900 Desktop Processor Series Specification Update".
Tested on SLBKP (2.8Ghz variant).  This should be a complete list of
bloomfield CPUs.

The change removes the only use of the ONLYMHZ flag, but I kept the flag
and the supporting code, since it might be useful in other situations.
